we report the case of a 7 monthold girl that presented with acute anemia generalized muscular hypotonia and failure to thrivelaboratory evaluation revealed cobalamin deficiency due to a vegan diet of the motherthe clinical triad of an acquired floppy baby syndrome with megaloblastic anemia and failure to thrive is pathognomic for infantile cobalamin deficiencyneurological abnormalities are often irreversible and may be associated with delayed myelinization in the mria normal cobalamin level in maternal serum and absence of anemia do not exclude subclinical deficiencyif cobalamin deficiency is suspected egin pregnant women on vegan diet urinary methylmalonic acid excretion and plasma homocysteine levels should be determined and cobalamin substitution should be started at an early stage to avoid potentially irreversible damage of the fetus